title: For Sale:  Swedish m40 Lahti 9mm Military Pistol
postcontent: This is a 9MM Swedish Model m40 9mm semi-auto pistol, sometimes referred to as a “Lahti” Pistol. Made in Sweden by Husqvarna, this was the standard Swedish Military sidearm from the 1940’s to Post-WWII. The Lahti is a unique semi-auto pistol, in that the trigger has an accellerator in it that allows the pistol to be fired in sub-zero conditions. The pistol has a blue factory finish and brown plastic checkered factory grips with the Hsqvarna logo. There are faint importers markings on the right front of the receiver, the Husqvarna markings are crisp and legible. The magazine is not marked. The pistol has heavy holster wear, wear on the grip straps, service marks, and there is a large spot of discoloration on top of the slide. The grips show minimal wear. The pistol has a nice, crisp bore, good rifling, and a smooth trigger pull.

title: For Sale:  C93 Rifle 5.56, Spare mags.
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Century C93 rifle, it is a clone of the HK93 rifle. I purchased this recently, however I wish to buy a .308 rifle and I need to raise some funds for that. This rifle is in good condition, and so are the surplus parts used in the build. The receiver is parkerized and the serial number is on top of the rifle, which means that it is from a batch of rifles that was built perfectly fine. I myself have not fired the rifle, and I don't think anyone else has. I have had the rifle disassembled to clean and oil it. I have not measured bolt gap. Everything does feel nice and tight though.

The rifle will come with one 40-round surplus magazine, and four 20-round polymer Pro-Mag mags. These mags fit out of the box and I didn't have to fit them to the rifle. It will also come with a HK surplus leather sling.

Asking $450. Located in NE Philadelphia, can do a FTF sale with a PA ID. Only trades I'm interested in are a C308 rifle, a PTR, or a Colt AR and I will toss in cash with the trade. PM if interested.

title: For Sale:  Temporary redirecting POP UP fix
postcontent:
Hey all, I found something that has  actually been working to stop the redirected website pop ups.
I am using an iPhone with Safari browser
When I select  'Minnesota', I get about 3 seconds before I am redirected out of Armslist. 
I have noticed that right before I am redirected, I can see the 'status bar' loading (quickly) at the top of my page. If I click the "X" on the far right, it stops the redirect by cancelling the page loader. I have to do this every time I enter Armslist, and again every time I advance pages. It suck, but it seems to be working. You have to be fast with it otherwise the redirect is inevitable! 
Just thought I would share what I learned-
No need for hate mail if you already knew this!
Feel free to let me know if it works for you, too. 
Good luck
